
Raspberry Pi 5: The central processing unit for running your algorithms.
RP LIDAR A2M12: For 2D mapping and obstacle detection.
Camera Module (Raspberry Pi Camera v2): For visual perception.
IMU Sensor MPU6050: For orientation and movement tracking.
Motor Driver L298N: To control the motors driving the wheels.
DC Motors with Encoders: For movement with feedback on the wheel position.
Power Supply: Batteries and power management circuits suitable for Raspberry Pi and the other components.
WiFi Dongle: For remote control and communication.*
Chassis: A durable frame with mounting points for sensors and the Raspberry Pi.
LEDs for Headlights, Brake Lights, Turn Signals: Simple visual indicators.
